💻 Practice Problem: FizzBuzz
📝 Problem Statement

Given an integer n, print:
🟢 "FizzBuzz" → if n is divisible by both 3 and 5
🟣 "Fizz" → if n is divisible only by 3
🟠 "Buzz" → if n is divisible only by 5
⚪ n → if none of the above conditions are true\
  | Input |  Output  |
| :---: | :------: |
|   3   |   Fizz   |
|   5   |   Buzz   |
|   15  | FizzBuzz |
|   7   |     7    |

  /////Solution/////
  #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;

    if (n % 3 == 0 && n % 5 == 0) {
        cout << "FizzBuzz" << endl;
    }
    else if (n % 3 == 0) {
        cout << "Fizz" << endl;
    }
    else if (n % 5 == 0) {
        cout << "Buzz" << endl;
    }
    else {
        cout << n << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
